description.p:
memory cells provided at cross sections of word lines and bit lines;


a word-line driver receiving a first power-supply voltage for driving the word lines in response to a first activation signal;


a delay circuit receiving a second power-supply voltage for generating a second activation signal that delays the first activation signal;


and a sense amplifier for amplifying the voltage read from the memory cell in response to the second activation signal;


wherein the second power-supply voltage is generated from the first power-supply voltage.
